reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great figures! Good value!
reviews.reviewText: I bought these for my son who is a FNAF fan, He loves them! He watches the music videos and has his lil figures dancing! and he loves the glowing changing colored lights! The price is great for getting 5 figures! These really are a cool thing! Get them for your FNAF fan!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's the generic FNAF crew, but def worth ur $$
reviews.reviewText: I used this for my son's 9th birthday birthday cake as cake toppers. I had got him his own smaller round cake and cupcakes for all the other kids that would be there. I definitely didn't expect the cake to be so small (like the size of a 1 year olds smash cake) my sister purchased it and I just knew it was going to be round white and red icing on top made to look like it was dripping down. It was actually a really nice cake. But since the characters were also surprisingly bigger than expected (which was the best part) they instead went around the cake. I think I got 5 or 6 in the pack. All we made great and he loves playing with them. They are all about 6 inches? Very good size for only about $20! They also each had a cool light on the front middle that flashes when u hold the button on their back down. Either way the real characters (him and the other kids def noticed right away) or not I'm super happy with my purchase 😊😊😊

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these as cake toppers for my son’s 11th birthday. My son loved them so much, he absconded with them to make stop action videos. He plays with these things on a regular basis and was super impressed by the cool light feature you get when you press the button on the back of each figure.Three things you should know before you order: First, these figures are not fully articulated but have basic points of articulation at the neck, shoulders, and hips. My son couldn’t care less that their waists, wrists, elbows, ankles, and knees don’t move. He says it makes them even more believable as animatronics! Second, we have had these about three months and a couple of them have small scratches on the surface paint, showing the base color underneath. Considering the hours of play he has put on them, the scratches are minimal. When I pointed them out to him, he rebutted, “FNAF animatronics aren’t supposed to look brand new. They’re supposed to look worn and torn!” Third, these aren’t licensed toys, so if that’s what you’re looking for, keep on looking! My child is pretty picky when it comes to brand name products and has licensed versions of all of these characters but these are still his go-to for play (and even display)! An excellent deal for the price, and FNAF fan approved. 5 stars!
